This paper deals with the identification of criminals and victims based on crime scene images, which is a problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed algorithm involves skin segmentation, key point localisation, image to template alignment, large feature set extraction, and classification, which are all techniques commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also deals with forensic investigation, which involves the use of technology to solve crimes. This could fall under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

The paper involves the use of image databases and image processing techniques, which could also fall under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques for classification, which could fall under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). 

Finally, the paper deals with the identification of criminals and victims, which could involve human-computer interaction and usability issues, falling under the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
